# Ordinal Logistic Regression for Toddler Nutritional Status

## 📌 Overview

This project presents an **Ordinal Logistic Regression** analysis to identify factors associated with toddler nutritional status. The response variable consists of three ordered categories: **Poor Nutrition**, **Under Nutrition**, and **Good Nutrition**.

The study evaluates the influence of birth weight, exclusive breastfeeding, and household sanitation on nutritional status.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

* Analyze factors affecting toddler nutritional status.
* Build an Ordinal Logistic Regression model.
* Interpret Odds Ratios for each predictor.
* Evaluate the predictive performance of the model.

---

## 📊 Variables

### Response Variable (Y)

**Toddler Nutritional Status**

* 1 = Poor Nutrition
* 2 = Under Nutrition
* 3 = Good Nutrition

### Predictor Variables (X)

| Variable | Description                                             |
| -------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| X1       | Birth Weight (0 = Low Birth Weight, 1 = Normal)         |
| X2       | Exclusive Breastfeeding (0 = No, 1 = Yes)               |
| X3       | Household Sanitation (0 = Good, 1 = Poor, 2 = Moderate) |

---

## 🛠️ Statistical Methods

* Descriptive Statistics
* Ordinal Logistic Regression
* Independence Test
* Odds Ratio Analysis
* Model Evaluation

---

## 📈 Key Results

### Significant Variables

* Birth Weight
* Exclusive Breastfeeding
* Household Sanitation

All predictor variables were statistically significant (**p < 0.001**).

### Odds Ratio

| Variable                      | Odds Ratio |
| ----------------------------- | ---------: |
| Normal Birth Weight           |     0.0241 |
| Exclusive Breastfeeding       |     0.0963 |
| Poor Household Sanitation     |    34.3321 |
| Moderate Household Sanitation |     7.0292 |

### Model Performance

* Classification Accuracy: **73%**
* Classification Error: **27%**

---

## 💡 Key Insights

* Normal birth weight reduces the likelihood of poor nutritional status.
* Exclusive breastfeeding has a protective effect on toddler nutritional status.
* Poor household sanitation substantially increases the risk of poor nutritional status.
* The developed model demonstrates good predictive performance with 73% accuracy.

